 system(s)
    you are working with - these are things that can change
    over time and what-not.
- you: Ok, so what are variables used for?
- ansible guru: Variables are a declarative definition of what
    your systems should be and/or can do.  Variables differ
    from facts in that they can be useful in playbooks to perform
    highly automated, sometimes dynamic or conditional tasks
    against remote systems, apply templating to config files,
    define things in playbooks that can change over time, the list
    goes on and on...and on...
- you: I get it.  But why do I need to know about any of this?
- ansible guru: Ansible is all about automation and consistency - think
    of all the duplicate work you could potentially save if you automated
    your configuration generation, deployment and/or maintenance via ans
